messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path: /printshop

- All HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD: true (Spring MVC provides automatic HEAD handling for endpoints that have a GET mapping, which this endpoint does)

- POST: false

- OPTIONS: true (Spring/MVC handles OPTIONS requests automatically for endpoints with mappings, providing an Allow header)

- TRACE: false

- GET: true (explicitly mapped in code)

- PUT: false

- DELETE: false

- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The ManagerController defines a single mapping for the path /printshop with method = RequestMethod.GET (getManagerPrintShop). There are no other annotations shaping a broader path prefix for this endpoint in this class, so the full path is exactly /printshop.
- Because there is a GET mapping for /printshop, HEAD requests are typically handled automatically by Spring by delegating to the GET handler; thus HEAD is considered acceptable.
- OPTIONS is generally handled by Spring for mapped endpoints by returning the allowed methods in the response; since /printshop has a GET mapping, OPTIONS is considered acceptable.
- All other HTTP methods (POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH) are not defined for /printshop in this code, so they are not acceptable.
- TRACE is not defined and is typically disabled unless explicitly enabled; thus not acceptable here.
